PAGE 6 — FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS (FAQ)
Use an accordion-style layout. Group questions into categories.

Category: Ordering
Q: How do I place an order?
You can order directly on our website, or send us a message on WhatsApp at +254 [NUMBER]. For WhatsApp orders, simply tell us what you'd like, your delivery address, and your preferred date and time.
Q: Can I customise my bouquet?
Absolutely! We love creating custom arrangements. Tell us your preferred flowers, colours, budget, and occasion via WhatsApp and our florists will design something uniquely for you.
Q: How far in advance should I order?
For same-day delivery, order before 1 PM. For special occasions like weddings, we recommend ordering at least 2–4 weeks in advance to guarantee availability.
Q: Can I include a personalised message?
Yes! There is a 'Add a message card' option on every product page and at checkout. We handwrite the card and include it with your bouquet at no extra charge.

Category: Delivery
Q: Do you offer same-day delivery?
Yes — we offer same-day delivery across Nairobi for orders placed before 1:00 PM, Monday to Saturday.
Q: What if no one is home to receive the flowers?
We will contact the recipient before delivery. If no one is available, we will leave the flowers in a safe, shaded location and send photo confirmation. Alternatively, we can reschedule at no extra charge.
Q: Do you deliver outside Nairobi?
Yes, we deliver to selected towns across Kenya including Mombasa, Kisumu, and Nakuru. Please contact us via WhatsApp for pricing and availability.
Q: Is delivery free?
Delivery is free on all orders over KES 3,000 within Nairobi. For smaller orders, a delivery fee applies — see our Delivery page for full details.

Category: Flowers & Quality
Q: How fresh are your flowers?
We source our flowers every morning from carefully selected farms. Your bouquet will typically be arranged within hours of your order being placed.
Q: How long will my flowers last?
With proper care, most of our cut flower arrangements will last 5–10 days. Orchids and tropical arrangements can last 2–3 weeks. Each bouquet comes with a care card.
Q: What if some flowers in my bouquet look different from the photo?
Flowers are a natural product and vary with the seasons. We may substitute one variety with a similar flower of equal or greater value to maintain the style, colour, and quality of the arrangement. We'll always let you know if a significant substitution is necessary.
Q: Are your flowers safe for pets?
Some flowers can be toxic to pets — particularly cats. If you have pets, please let us know and we will avoid lilies (toxic to cats), tulips, and other potentially harmful blooms. Sunflowers, roses, and orchids are generally safe choices.

Category: Payments
Q: What payment methods do you accept?
We accept M-Pesa (Paybill / Till Number), Visa, Mastercard, and cash on delivery for select Nairobi areas.
Q: Is it safe to pay online?
Yes. Our website uses SSL encryption and all card payments are processed through a secure, PCI-compliant payment gateway. We never store your card details.
Q: Can I pay on delivery?
Cash on delivery is available for selected areas in Nairobi. Please select this option at checkout and our team will confirm availability.

Category: Cancellations & Returns
Q: Can I cancel or change my order?
Cancellations and changes must be made at least 4 hours before the scheduled delivery time. Please contact us immediately via WhatsApp or phone. We cannot cancel orders that have already been prepared or are out for delivery.
Q: What if I am not happy with my flowers?
Your satisfaction is our top priority. If your flowers arrive damaged or are not as described, please take a photo and contact us within 24 hours. We will replace your arrangement or provide a full refund — whichever you prefer.

 
PAGE 7 — REFUND & RETURNS POLICY
💡 NOTE: This is a legal/policy page. Use clear, plain language. This copy can be adapted by your legal team.

Overview
At [Brand Name], your satisfaction is our promise. Because flowers are perishable, our return and refund policy is designed to be fair to both you and our team. Please read this policy carefully before placing your order.

Satisfaction Guarantee
We stand behind every bouquet we create. If your flowers arrive damaged, wilted, or significantly different from what was ordered — we will replace the arrangement free of charge or issue a full refund. No questions asked.

What Qualifies for a Refund or Replacement
•	Flowers arrived visibly damaged or wilted upon delivery
•	The arrangement was significantly different from what was ordered (wrong flowers, wrong size, wrong colour)
•	The order was not delivered on the promised date due to our error
💡 NOTE: Issues must be reported within 24 hours of delivery with clear photographs sent via WhatsApp or email.

What Does Not Qualify
•	Minor natural colour variations between the photo and the actual flowers (flowers are a natural product and vary by season and availability)
•	Flowers that have wilted due to improper care by the recipient after delivery
•	Flowers left unattended in the sun or heat after delivery
•	Orders where the incorrect delivery address was provided
•	Change of mind after the arrangement has been prepared

Cancellation Policy
Orders can be cancelled free of charge up to 4 hours before the scheduled delivery time. Cancellations made less than 4 hours before delivery will incur a 50% cancellation fee, as the arrangement will already have been prepared. Orders that have already been dispatched cannot be cancelled.

Refund Processing
Approved refunds are processed within 3–5 business days to your original payment method. M-Pesa refunds are typically instant once approved. Card refunds may take up to 7 business days depending on your bank.

How to Request a Refund or Replacement
•	Step 1: Take clear photographs of the flowers immediately upon receiving them.
•	Step 2: Contact us within 24 hours via WhatsApp (+254 [NUMBER]) or email (info@[domain].co.ke).
•	Step 3: Include your order number, name, and description of the issue.
•	Step 4: Our team will review and respond within 2 business hours during working hours.
•	Step 5: We will arrange a replacement delivery or process your refund.

Flower Freshness Guarantee
Our cut flower arrangements are guaranteed to be fresh for a minimum of 5 days from the delivery date, provided they are cared for following the instructions on the care card included with your order. Orchids and tropical arrangements are guaranteed for 14 days.

 
