Full Blog Outline 1 — Flower Meanings by Colour
SEO Title:
The Complete Guide to Flower Meanings by Colour and Type (2025)
Meta Description:
Discover what every flower colour means — from red roses for love to white lilies for peace. The ultimate guide to choosing the right flowers for any occasion in Nairobi.
Introduction:
Flowers have spoken a secret language for centuries — called 'floriography.' Understanding what different flowers and colours mean helps you choose a gift that says exactly what you feel, without a single word.
Section 1 — Red Flowers:
Meaning: Love, passion, desire. Best for: Valentine's Day, anniversaries, romantic gestures. Top flowers: Red roses, red tulips, red gerberas.
Section 2 — Pink Flowers:
Meaning: Admiration, gratitude, femininity. Best for: Mother's Day, birthdays, thank-you gifts. Top flowers: Pink roses, peonies, pink carnations.
Section 3 — White Flowers:
Meaning: Purity, peace, new beginnings. Best for: Weddings, sympathy, new baby. Top flowers: White lilies, white roses, white orchids.
Section 4 — Yellow Flowers:
Meaning: Friendship, joy, cheerfulness. Best for: Birthdays, congratulations, get well. Top flowers: Sunflowers, yellow roses, daffodils.
Section 5 — Purple/Lavender Flowers:
Meaning: Royalty, admiration, elegance. Best for: Milestone events, corporate gifts. Top flowers: Purple orchids, lavender, purple irises.
Section 6 — Mixed Bouquets:
Meaning: Versatile, colourful, celebratory. Best for: Any occasion — when in doubt, go mixed.
