Full Blog Outline 2 — How to Keep Flowers Fresh
SEO Title:
How to Keep Cut Flowers Fresh Longer — 10 Expert Tips From Our Florists
Intro:
You've just received a beautiful bouquet and want it to last as long as possible. Here are the insider tips our florists use every day.
Tip 1:
Cut the stems at a 45-degree angle with a sharp, clean knife or scissors. This increases the surface area for water absorption.
Tip 2:
Remove any leaves that fall below the waterline. Submerged leaves rot quickly and introduce bacteria.
Tip 3:
Use a clean vase. Bacteria in an unwashed vase is the number one cause of early wilting.
Tip 4:
Add flower food (included in your order). It contains sugar for energy, acidifier to improve water uptake, and biocide to fight bacteria.
Tip 5:
Change the water every 2 days and re-cut the stems each time.
Tip 6:
Keep flowers away from direct sunlight, radiators, and air conditioning vents.
Tip 7:
Store in a cool room overnight if possible — flowers love cool temperatures.
Tip 8:
Keep flowers away from fruit. Ripening fruit releases ethylene gas which causes flowers to age faster.
Tip 9:
Don't place flowers near cigarette smoke or strong fumes.
Tip 10:
Spritz the petals lightly with water for extra freshness — especially for roses.
